### knowledge base (http_request + notion connector)
- `POST /v1/databases/{database_id}/query` with filter:
```
{ "filter": { "and": [ { "property": "Review Due Date", "date": { "on_or_before": "YYYY-MM-DD" } }, { "property": "Review Status", "select": { "does_not_equal": "Reviewed" } }
] } }
```
- `PATCH /v1/pages/{page_id}` body:
```
{ "properties": { "Last Reviewed": { "date": { "start": "YYYY-MM-DD" } }, "Review Due Date": { "date": { "start": "YYYY-MM-DD" } }, "Review Status": { "select": { "name": "Current" } }
} }
```
Headers: `Authorization: Bearer {integration_token}`, `knowledge base-Version: 2022-06-28`. ### messaging (http_request + slack connector)
- `POST /api/chat.postMessage` formatted messaging layout: header, section (new assignments with @reviewer tags), section (overdue), actions (KB link button).
- Completion shoutouts: mrkdwn with:white_check_mark: and next-due date.
Headers: `Authorization: Bearer {bot_token}`. ### email (gmail_send native tool)
- Reminder: subject 'Knowledge Base Review Request: [Title]'; HTML body includes direct knowledge base URL, deadline, review criteria, completion instructions.
- Overdue follow-up: gentler tone, reference original assignment date, link, re-deadline.
- BCC admin address for audit trail. ### Local state (file_read / file_write)
-./kb_review_state.json — rotation_index, assignments map, completed_log, last_run_timestamp. Write after every side effect. ### Review frequency math
Monthly = +30d, Quarterly = +90d, Semi = +180d, Annually = +365d, Custom = +{Custom Review Days}. Always compute from completion date, not original due date.
